title: Sidewall - Fragment, 1850
provenance: Background of pattern rotted away. This portion was fourth oldest layer of wallpaper in ground floor room, Hurd House, built from 1680 on, Woodbury, Connecticut.
description: There is no pattern remaining on this top layer of paper. The surface has the appearance of a woodgrain or moire pattern but is actually worm eaten. The layer below has an indiscernable pattern. Possibly a rainbow or irise paper, it is printed in shades of blue.

tombstone.epitaph: Sidewall - Fragment, 1850. Machine-printed and worm eaten. 1968-66-9.
